ok ok today was prolly the most horrific day ive had ever. im basically gonna explain what happened and most of you will not understand wtf im saying and the ones that do are lying... Spanning-Tree Protocol is a link management protocol that provides path redundancy while preventing undesirable loops in the network. For an Ethernet network to function properly, only one active path can exist between two stations. Multiple active paths between stations cause loops in the network. If a loop exists in the network topology, the potential exists for duplication of messages. When loops occur, some switches see stations appear on both sides of the switch. This condition confuses the forwarding algorithm and allows duplicate frames to be forwarded. so basically spanning tree is supposed to prevent loops in the network...or so it seems. we dont know how or where but we do know it was sometime this morning someone plugged a crossover cable (568a on one end and 568b on the other) into a port somewhere in shoreline. that basically sent spanning tree into a loop which built up and caused denial of service on all our cisco 3550 switches. thats about 60 switches. so for most of the day we were trying to find out where this happened.we had to manually reset all those switches which was really fun!!! so yeah cisco couldnt figure out how to fix it and theyre the ones who made the damn switch. so needless to say i loathe spanning tree with the passion of the christ!! it was a long day at work but thats ok and im on call tonight so that means ill prolly get called in or something or other.it coo though i dont care and i eagerly await what tomorrow will bring. so here are some pics of waht im talking about i would go more into detail but that would confuse the shit outta most of you. -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------i completely forgot!! some of you might be wondering why the hell we use spanning tree. well... our NOS (network operating system) novell, has gotten to the point where we can install winxp pro of the network. basically thats why we use spanning tree. damn novell zenworks, damn u in the butt!!
